No spoilers.. but don’t expect this to go well..

2tihCUXypaU.title: Running a 5K while under the influence
2tihCUXypaU.description:
I ran cross country in 7th grade and I absolutely hated it. 
I ran cross country again in 8th grade just to be sure, and I still hated it. 

I live a relatively active lifestyle and I’m able to maintain that while staying far away from treadmills and ellipticals. 

However, my mother runs often. Her 2019 resolution was to run three 5Ks (3.1mi) a week, and I made the mistake of telling her I’d run the last one with her. So on December 31st we geared up for the Resolution Run, a traditional 5K run with a non traditional twist. My mom had fun, my dad and I didn’t, and Ashley was there for moral support (she wasn’t “medically cleared” to run). 

We did, however, all get to drink beer. So there’s always that..
